TITLE: Creating Custom Particle Processor Class in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines a custom particle processor class that extends the Phaser.GameObjects.Particles.ParticleProcessor class. The update method allows for custom particle behavior modifications during each frame.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rexrainbow/phaser3-rex-notes/blob/master/docs/docs/particles.md#2025-04-21_snippet_42

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class MyParticleProcessor extends Phaser.GameObjects.Particles.ParticleProcessor {
    constructor() {
        super(x, y, active);
        // ...
    }

    update(particle, delta, step, t) {
        // particle : The Particle to update.
        // delta : The delta time in ms.
        // step : The delta value divided by 1000.
        // t : The current normalized lifetime of the particle, between 0 (birth) and 1 (death).
    }

    destroy() {
        super.destroy();
    }
}
```

